post_text:
Friday's Guidelines at Knox County for HS Football:
Visitor seating will be on the east side of the field.

Bleacher seating is limited, but spectators are welcome to bring chairs and sit on the track.

They are not operating a concessions stand, but spectators are welcome to bring coolers, food, and non-alcoholic drinks.

Masks are encouraged when social distancing is not possible.

The game will be live streamed. The link will be provided on the KCR1 website ( https://www.knox.k12.mo.us ).

No charge for admission, but free will donations are welcome to help offset the cost of officials and game workers.

shared_text:
Linn County Health Department
September 4 at 4:27 PM ·

It has been determined a COVID-19 positive case attended the high school football game at Chester Ray Stadium in Marceline, MO on Friday, August 28th during their contagious period.

We are working to assess close contacts; however, we are asking all individuals who also attended the game to self monitor for symptoms. If you have COVID-19 symptoms we ask you to please not go out in public. Call your primary care provider for the best way to seek care if symptoms do develop.

Prom Announcement from Mr. Finch Prom Dance at the Ag building parking lot from 8-11 on July 11. There will be no grand march or after prom. post_text:
KWIX, KRES, KIRK, KTCM Radio has provided a page on their website at centralmoinfo.com where you can post your Graduates picture. Click on the banner 'Area Graduates' and then select 'Surrounding Counties 2020 Graduates' and share your graduate's photo along with a personal message or information about your graduate. The message could also include accomplishments and/or their plans following graduation.

Graduation is a milestone everyone looks forward to. But for the class of 2020, this year will be one they never forget. Unfortunately, many will not be able to participate in the traditional ceremony, but that doesn't mean their accomplishments should go unnoticed. That's why we're inviting you to share photos of your graduate, whether they're graduating from high school, college, 8th grade, kindergarten, or preschool. Log on to centralmoinfo.com today to upload your photo and let everyone know how proud you are. Photos will appear within 24 hours of submission.

As the first case of Coronavirus is diagnosed in Missouri, more are likely to follow soon. We will continue to work with the Health Department and follow our pandemic flu plan. Increased cleaning procedures have already been taking place due to the normal influenza season and will continue as we weather this new virus. Please follow the information closely and stay home if you are sick.

Good handwashing practices continues to be our best defense against the spread of disease, so make sure you and your family are washing your hands frequently for at least 20 seconds. If you have any questions or concerns, contact Nurse Kelly.

post_text: The Marceline R-V School District has an opening for a Special Education Paraprofessional. Minimum Qualifications: Completed at least two years of study (60 credit hours) at an institution of higher education or met a rigorous standard of quality demonstrated through a Paraprofessional Praxis test. Qualified candidates must also pass a background check required by Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education. This is an hourly position with full benefits. Information may be obtained by contacting Dawn Lichtenberg, Federal Programs Office, Marceline R-V School District, 400 E Santa Fe, Marceline, MO 64658. Phone 660-376-6010. Applications are available on the district website, www.marcelineschools.org. Position open until filled. Marceline R-V is an equal opportunity employer.

post_text:
As we return to school next week, Nurse Kelly wants to remind you when to keep your children home with illness. Right now, along with colds and viruses, influenza and strep are circulating in the area. If your family has recently been ill, please wash or disinfect their coat, backpack and lunchbox. Weekly cleaning or disinfecting with Lysol can help kill germs on these items as well. However, frequent HANDWASHING practices is still your best defense against illness!

Everyone wants perfect attendance at work or school, but if your child is sick or you are sick, please stay home.

post_text: The Marceline R-V School District has an opening for a Special Education Paraprofessional. Minimum Qualifications: Completed at least two years of study (60 credit hours) at an institution of higher education or met a rigorous standard of quality demonstrated through a Paraprofessional Praxis test. Qualified candidates must also pass a background check required by Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education. This is an hourly position with full benefits. Information may be obtained by contacting Dawn Lichtenberg, Federal Programs Office, Marceline R-V School District, 400 E Santa Fe, Marceline, MO 64658. Phone 660-376-6010. Applications are available on the district website, www.marcelineschools.org. Position open until filled. Marceline R-V is an equal opportunity employer.

post_text: PEP BUS – Students in grades 9-12 are invited to sign-up to ride on a pep bus Friday and/or Saturday depending on tournament results. Marceline will play at 1:00 pm on Friday. If they win, they will play at 2:00 pm on Saturday. If they lose, they will play again on Friday at 5:00 pm. The pep bus will be going back and forth from Marceline to Springfield daily. Students who sign up for either or both pep bus rides will be asked to pay $10/trip. This will include their $8 gate entry fee for the MSHSAA State Softball event. Students will also need money for food and drinks throughout the day. Information will be sent to students through the high school office. (A minimum number of participants will be required before the pep bus will be sent to Springfield.) Students must sign up by 2:00 pm on Tuesday if they would like to ride.

Their presentation highlighted grade level testing results in comparison to historical data as well as to the district’s performance in comparison to state testing results.
